cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the virtualization of Radio Access Networks and the placement and assignment of servers in such networks. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses the implementation of Base Band Units (BBUs) in a shared infrastructure located at either a data center or distributed in network nodes. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper mentions the objective of minimizing latency between each Remote Radio Head (RRH) and its assigned BBU. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with the optimization of server and front haul link setup costs. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper discusses the simulation of algorithms to compare their solution quality and computation time under varying network sizes and setup budgets.
